  Then you see it an oasis shimmers in the distance — a glistening pond 
surrounded by palm trees.

  "Look, look!" you say to Ahmed. Ahmed is strangely calm.

  "I'm sorry, but that is just a mirage — a trick the desert plays on the eyes,
my friend," he says.

  After another mile or so of hiking, you realize that Ahmed is right. Nothing
is there. Sheets of water seem to materialize, then vanish after you have 
walked a few yards.

  A few hours later, you stop suddenly. "Ahmed, am I crazy or do I hear thunder
in the distance? Are there sound mirages in the desert?"




